ormal; font-variant-emoji: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;\"><br \/><\/span><\/div><\/span>","padding_top":0,"padding_bottom":0,"reset_spacing":false}},"faq_j4pm6T":{"type":"faq","blocks":{"faq_7kLypm":{"type":"faq","settings":{"title":"How big should a lamp be over a table?","content":"<p>A table lamp should be proportional to the table it sits on. The lamp should be about 1.5 times the height of the table, with the lampshade at eye level for optimal lighting and comfort.<\/p>"}},"faq_J3YAhD":{"type":"faq","settings":{"title":"Are table lamps still in style?","content":"<p>Yes, table lamps remain timeless and versatile. Trendy styles like industrial, modern, and brass table lamps suit various design aesthetics.<\/p>"}},"faq_r4a7H7":{"type":"faq","settings":{"title":"Do table lamps use less electricity?","content":"<p>Yes, table lamps consume less electricity than overhead lights, especially when fitted with LED bulbs.<\/p>"}},"faq_pwLcLP":{"type":"faq","settings":{"title":"Is it cheaper to run a lamp or a main light?","content":"<p>Running a table lamp is generally cheaper than a main light. For added savings, choose energy-efficient options like LED touch table lamps.<\/p>"}}},"block_order":["faq_7kLypm","faq_J3YAhD","faq_r4a7H7","faq_pwLcLP"],"disabled":true,"settings":{"heading":"Frequently Asked Questions","description":"","text_alignment":"text-center","container":"container","background_color":"","padding_top":0,"padding_bottom":0,"reset_spacing":false}}},"order":["main-collection-heading","8498460c-0376-40d1-bafc-199edbe0edfc","439e38df-206c-40a8-9cd5-fc0e5f00f9d3","product-grid","b1a1633c-9de0-43c8-8a60-a0eddc69dfb1","47b4aaae-a5a7-401b-a79c-d7b0652caf69","divider_PhNww8","custom_text_qedYj9","banner_image_bUhTqD","custom_liquid_BPkHwA","gallery_rdw6wK","custom_liquid_NKDQi4","custom_liquid_NwqKTf","faq_j4pm6T"]}